T1  - Information Technology, Manpower Development and Organizational Performance
AU  - Baum, Bernard
AU  - Burack, Elmer
Y1  - 1969/09/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255176
DO  - 10.5465/255176
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 279
EP  - 291
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study of some 70 large business firms suggests that many companies, some of considerable size, continue to reflect a lack of appreciation for uses of information technology in managerial decision systems and the implications of this innovation for managerial education and training. This research additionally confirms the necessary organizational rearrangements and attendant programs at all organization levels which accompany the successful extension of computer based systems.
AB  - This study of some 70 large business firms suggests that many companies, some of considerable size, continue to reflect a lack of appreciation for uses of information technology in managerial decision systems and the implications of this innovation for managerial education and training. This research additionally confirms the necessary organizational rearrangements and attendant programs at all organization levels which accompany the successful extension of computer based systems.
