TY  - JOUR
T1  - Sigma Iota Epsilon: The Academy's Student Division: Opportunity and Dilemma for the Management Professor
AU  - Bernthal, Wilmar F.
Y1  - 1969/09/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255184
DO  - 10.5465/255184
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 379
EP  - 381
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article reports on college students' power within their school and their ability to impact professors and the administration. Most professors typically have little to gain from undergraduate students' achievement and students have limited capability to influence this social force. Sigma Iota Epsilon, a student division of the Academy of Management, is described for the changes and development. Management professors and graduate business students have begun playing a larger role in the student division. Membership is based on academic achievement and the group is focusing on previously unexplored topics.
AB  - The article reports on college students' power within their school and their ability to impact professors and the administration. Most professors typically have little to gain from undergraduate students' achievement and students have limited capability to influence this social force. Sigma Iota Epsilon, a student division of the Academy of Management, is described for the changes and development. Management professors and graduate business students have begun playing a larger role in the student division. Membership is based on academic achievement and the group is focusing on previously unexplored topics.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255184
